"MindSettler Privacy Policy",
 
About Your Privacy and This Privacy Policy
Your privacy is extremely important to us. At MindSettler, we put significant thought, effort, tools, resources, and procedures in place to protect and safeguard your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose information you provide while using our Platform and services.

Information Collection, Use, and Disclosure
We may collect:
- Personal Information: name, email, phone number, login credentials.
- Session Information: booking details, preferences, session communication.
- Health-Related Data: information shared during counseling sessions.
- Usage Data: how you interact with the website, chatbot, and services.

Information is used to:
- Contact you about services, bookings, or updates.
- Billing and payment processing.
- Match you with a Counselor and facilitate services.
- Monitor, supervise, and improve the Platform and services.
- Ensure safety and comply with legal obligations.

Cookies
We use cookies to enhance user experience. You can adjust your browser settings to refuse cookies, but some services may be limited.

Phishing & Online Security
MindSettler will never request your login or payment details via insecure or unsolicited channels.

Third-Party Links
We may link to external websites. We are not responsible for their content, privacy policies, or practices.

Data Security
We use industry-standard security measures including encryption and secure servers. No online system is 100% secure.

Service Providers
Third-party providers may help facilitate our services. Only minimal necessary information is shared under confidentiality agreements.

Children's Privacy
Our services are for children above 5 with parental consent and adults. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 5.

International Transfer
Your data may be transferred and stored outside your state or country. We maintain secure handling of such data.

Compliance with Laws
We may disclose information as required by law to protect safety or comply with legal obligations. Counselors may be required to report abuse, suicidal risk, threats to others, or court-ordered requests.


Changes
We may update this Privacy Policy at our discretion. Updates will always be posted on the Platform.



